-- Magnitude 5.1 earthquake strikes southern California -USGS
-- 
-- Sat Mar 29, 2014 12:28AM EDT
-- None



LOS ANGELES, March 28 (Reuters) - A magnitude 5.1 earthquake struck the Los Angeles area in southern California on Friday, the U.S. Geological Survey said.

The quake, initially reported as a magnitude 5.3, was very shallow, only 1.2 miles (2 km) deep, with its epicenter located just 2 miles (3 km) east of the town of La Habra and some 27 miles (43 km) from Long Beach.